00:51:43,060 --> 00:51:43,960
 Lord, let it be.

1307
00:51:43,960 --> 00:51:46,400
 So God, thank you,

1308
00:51:46,400 --> 00:51:52,100
 that while we were a long way off, you came for us.

1309
00:51:53,700 --> 00:51:55,060
 And God, I know there's some people in here

1310
00:51:55,060 --> 00:51:57,700
 that have never put their faith in Jesus.

1311
00:51:57,700 --> 00:52:01,660
 And I pray that first part of the sermon

1312
00:52:01,660 --> 00:52:03,060
 would be for them, that they would say,

1313
00:52:03,060 --> 00:52:04,180
 no, I know what I am.

1314
00:52:04,180 --> 00:52:07,260
 I know I'm dead, and I keep trying to turn over a new leaf,

1315
00:52:07,260 --> 00:52:11,220
 but I need to be resurrected.

1316
00:52:11,220 --> 00:52:15,900
 And thank you, God, that you sent Christ,

1317
00:52:15,900 --> 00:52:18,300
 that he can renovate hearts from the inside out.

1318
00:52:18,300 --> 00:52:23,580
 And Lord, I pray there might be some men and women

1319
00:52:23,580 --> 00:52:25,540
 here even tonight that say, I want you.

1320
00:52:25,540 --> 00:52:28,800
 If you're rescuing, rescue me.

1321
00:52:28,800 --> 00:52:32,600
 If you're reweaving the severed fabric

1322
00:52:32,600 --> 00:52:36,300
 between heaven and earth, weave me in.

1323
00:52:36,300 --> 00:52:40,460
 You tell him that tonight, friend,

1324
00:52:40,460 --> 00:52:42,020
 and then please tell one of us.

1325
00:52:42,020 --> 00:52:46,040
 And then God, for those of us who know you,

1326
00:52:46,040 --> 00:52:48,620
 it's not shocking to watch a culture divide

1327
00:52:48,620 --> 00:52:52,340
 of along very common lines, all throughout human stories,

1328
00:52:52,340 --> 00:52:54,720
 we have divided across cultures.

1329
00:52:54,720 --> 00:52:58,540
 Decided on socioeconomic boundaries,

1330
00:52:58,540 --> 00:53:01,100
 political boundaries, ethnic boundaries, we divide.

1331
00:53:01,100 --> 00:53:05,300
 But God, you have done something about that too.

1332
00:53:05,300 --> 00:53:07,620
 The cross is so powerful.

1333
00:53:07,620 --> 00:53:09,800
 It not only brings the dead to life,

1334
00:53:09,800 --> 00:53:12,900
 it makes enemies into family.

1335
00:53:12,900 --> 00:53:16,220
 So I pray, God, in the midst of a culture that's divided,

1336
00:53:16,220 --> 00:53:18,380
 might they see us speak the truth to each other?

1337
00:53:18,380 --> 00:53:22,200
 Not hide it, not bury it, but speak it in love,

1338
00:53:22,200 --> 00:53:26,260
 with gentleness and humility, with patience,

1339
00:53:26,260 --> 00:53:29,560
 bearing with one another, eager to maintain that unity.

1340
00:53:29,560 --> 00:53:32,880
 And I pray, God, radiating out of our churches

1341
00:53:32,880 --> 00:53:34,500
 and towns all across this country,

1342
00:53:34,500 --> 00:53:37,340
 people would see, surely God is in their midst.

1343
00:53:37,340 --> 00:53:40,180
 What could create a healing like that?

1344
00:53:40,180 --> 00:53:42,740
 What kind of balm could heal the wounds

1345
00:53:42,740 --> 00:53:43,840
 of a nation like that?

1346
00:53:43,840 --> 00:53:47,340
 God, I pray the glory of all that you purchased

1347
00:53:47,340 --> 00:53:50,260
 on the cross would be manifest through the unity

1348
00:53:50,260 --> 00:53:53,320
 we persevere and maintain together.

1349
00:53:53,320 --> 00:53:56,360
 Knit us together for your glory,

1350
00:53:56,360 --> 00:53:58,700
 knit us together for our good,

1351
00:53:58,700 --> 00:54:02,620
 and may our cities be different because we exist.

1352
00:54:02,620 --> 00:54:09,640
 May this generation be different

1353
00:54:09,640 --> 00:54:11,540
 because we dare to believe this truth.

1354
00:54:17,040 --> 00:54:19,860
 I wanna invite you just to ask Him,

1355
00:54:19,860 --> 00:54:21,660
 what would it look like for me, God,

1356
00:54:21,660 --> 00:54:24,120
 to forgive someone who hurt me,

1357
00:54:24,120 --> 00:54:27,440
 to reach out to someone I've avoided,

1358
00:54:27,440 --> 00:54:32,460
 to pray for somebody that I secretly just wanna see fall.

1359
00:54:32,460 --> 00:54:34,620
 What if I prayed and asked God to bless me?

1360
00:54:34,620 --> 00:54:38,880
 To not give up when people are a hassle,

1361
00:54:38,880 --> 00:54:43,180
 to press in with a question

1362
00:54:43,180 --> 00:54:44,980
 rather than attack with a statement,

1363
00:54:46,740 --> 00:54:49,000
 ask Him to give you a vision of what it might look like

1364
00:54:49,000 --> 00:54:50,700
 to be the church to each other.

1365
00:54:50,700 --> 00:54:57,720
 Let it be.

1366
00:54:57,720 --> 00:55:07,720
 [BLANK_AUDIO]

